   2         0                            ;   math.asm -- arithmetic / logical / shift / DBR-loop coverage
   3         0                            ;
   4         0                            ;   Exercises a broader slice of the IEEE-draft 68000 opcode set than
   5         0                            ;   bubble.asm: AND, OR, XOR, SHL.L, SHRA.L, DBR, and DATA.L (the last
   6         0                            ;   of which was broken in the original 1990 code — this fixture is
   7         0                            ;   also the regression test for that fix).
   8         0                            ;
   9         0                            ;   The program writes eight 32-bit result words to RESLOC:
  10         0                            ;
  11         0                            ;     [0]  sum   of ARRAY[0..N-1]
  12         0                            ;     [1]  AND   of ARRAY[0..N-1]
  13         0                            ;     [2]  OR    of ARRAY[0..N-1]
  14         0                            ;     [3]  XOR   of ARRAY[0..N-1]   (running parity)
  15         0                            ;     [4]  X + Y                    (scalar)
  16         0                            ;     [5]  X - Y
  17         0                            ;     [6]  X << 2                   (SHL.L  #2,Dn)
  18         0                            ;     [7]  X >> 2 arithmetic        (SHRA.L #2,Dn)
